","1427":"1427","Raith, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Skotland, United Kingdom","Caproneston, Peebleshire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Skotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Skotland, United Kingdom","Raith, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Fife, Skotland, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Fife, Skotland, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"ABT 1320–before 5 July 1365":"circa 1320–vóór 5 juli 1365","1320–1365":"1320–1365","1332–1365":"1332–1365","1346–1427":"1346–1427","1364–1427":"1364–1427","1287–1345":"1287–1345","–Female":"Overleden","after 1346":"na 1346","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","ABT 1320":"circa 1320","1332":"1332","1365":"1365","1364":"1364","1287":"1287","1320":"1320","before 5 July 1365":"vóór 5 juli 1365","1427":"1427","Raith, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Caproneston, Peebleshire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Scotland":"Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Raith, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Fife, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Fife, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"ABT 1320–before 5 July 1365":"about 1320–before 5 July 1365","1320–1365":"1320–1365","1332–1365":"1332–1365","1346–1427":"1346–1427","1364–1427":"1364–1427","1287–1345":"1287–1345","–Female":"Deceased","after 1346":"after 1346","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","ABT 1320":"about 1320","1332":"1332","1365":"1365","1364":"1364","1287":"1287","1320":"1320","before 5 July 1365":"before 5 July 1365","1427":"1427","Raith, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom","Caproneston, Peebleshire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","Raith, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Melville","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): habitational name from any of the various places in Normandy called Malleville, from Latin <i>mala</i> ‘bad’ + <i>ville</i> ‘settlement’.","Irish (mainly Ulster): English surname adopted by bearers of Gaelic <b>Ó Maoilmhichíl</b> ‘descendant of <i>Maoilmhichil</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘devotee of (Saint) Michael’.","History: The American novelist Herman Melville (1819–91) was a descendantof the Scottish Melvilles. His maternal grandfather was the revolutionary war general Peter Gansevoort (born 1749 in Albany, NY). His paternal grandfather was Maj. Thomas Melville of Boston. Irish bearers of the name claim descent from Maol Mhichíl, a chief of Síol Muireadhaigh (County Roscommon) in the 9th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Melvin","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): variant of   Melville   with alternation of final <i>-l</i> and <i>-n</i>.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Maoil Mhín</b> ‘descendant of the devotee of Maoilmhín’, a personal name meaning ‘gentle chieftain’."]},{"name":"Mulville","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Melville  ."]},{"name":"Mellin","meanings":["Scottish (Glamorgan): variant of   Melville  .","German: habitational name from any of various places so called.","English: variant of   Melling  ."]},{"name":"Mulvihill","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Paddy.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Maoil Mhichíl</b> ‘descendant of the devotee of (Saint) Michael’. The Anglicized form was sometimes abbreviated into   Melville  ."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Walter Melville was born about 1320, in Peeblesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom as the son of John Melville and Stewart. He had at least 2 sons with Margaret Ayr. He died before 5 July 1365, in Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"ABT 1320–before 5 July 1365":"umbes 1320–enne 5. juulit 1365","1320–1365":"1320–1365","1332–1365":"1332–1365","1346–1427":"1346–1427","1364–1427":"1364–1427","1287–1345":"1287–1345","–Female":"Surnud","after 1346":"pärast 1346","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","ABT 1320":"umbes 1320","1332":"1332","1365":"1365","1364":"1364","1287":"1287","1320":"1320","before 5 July 1365":"enne 5. juulit 1365","1427":"1427","Raith, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Caproneston, Peebleshire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Raith, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1320–before 5 July 1365":"noin 1320–ennen vuotta 5. heinäkuuta 1365","1320–1365":"1320–1365","1332–1365":"1332–1365","1346–1427":"1346–1427","1364–1427":"1364–1427","1287–1345":"1287–1345","–Female":"Kuollut","after 1346":"1346 jälkeen","1346":"1346","1345":"1345","ABT 1320":"noin 1320","1332":"1332","1365":"1365","1364":"1364","1287":"1287","1320":"1320","before 5 July 1365":"ennen vuotta 5. heinäkuuta 1365","1427":"1427","Raith, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Caproneston, Peebleshire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Raith, Fifeshire, Scotland":"Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1320–before 5 July 1365":"environ 1320–avant 5 juillet 1365","1320–1365":"1320–1365","1332–1365":"1332–1365","1346–14